json.creator: Lawrence Abrams
json.title: Microsoft: Windows 10 KB5072653 OOB update fixes ESU install errors
json.dc:creator: Lawrence Abrams
json.content: Microsoft has released an emergency Windows 10 KB5072653 out-of-band update to resolve ongoing issues with installing the November extended security updates. [...]
json.contentSnippet: Microsoft has released an emergency Windows 10 KB5072653 out-of-band update to resolve ongoing issues with installing the November extended security updates. [...]

json.creator: Bill Toulas
json.title: Malicious NPM packages abuse Adspect redirects to evade security
json.dc:creator: Bill Toulas
json.content: Seven packages published on the Node Package Manager (npm) registry use the Adspect cloud-based service to separate researchers from potential victims and lead them to malicious locations. [...]
json.contentSnippet: Seven packages published on the Node Package Manager (npm) registry use the Adspect cloud-based service to separate researchers from potential victims and lead them to malicious locations. [...]

json.title: xAI's Grok 4.1 rolls out with improved quality and speed for free
json.dc:creator: Mayank Parmar
json.content: Elon Musk-owned xAI has started rolling out Grok 4.1, which is an upgrade to the existing Grok 4 model, and it delivers some incremental improvements. [...]

json.title: Google Gemini 3 spotted on AI Studio ahead of imminent release

json.creator: Bill Toulas
json.title: Eurofiber France warns of breach after hacker tries to sell customer data
json.dc:creator: Bill Toulas
json.content: Eurofiber France disclosed a data breach it discovered late last week when hackers gained access to its ticket management system by exploiting a vulnerability and exfiltrated information. [...]
json.contentSnippet: Eurofiber France disclosed a data breach it discovered late last week when hackers gained access to its ticket management system by exploiting a vulnerability and exfiltrated information. [...]

json.creator: Sergiu Gatlan
json.title: Princeton University discloses data breach affecting donors, alumni
json.dc:creator: Sergiu Gatlan
json.content: A Princeton University database was compromised in a cyberattack on November 10, exposing the personal information of alumni, donors, faculty members, and students. [...]
json.contentSnippet: A Princeton University database was compromised in a cyberattack on November 10, exposing the personal information of alumni, donors, faculty members, and students. [...]

json.creator: Bill Toulas
json.title: Dutch police seizes 250 servers used by “bulletproof hosting” service
json.dc:creator: Bill Toulas
json.content: The police in the Netherlands have seized around 250 physical servers powering a bulletproof hosting service in the country used exclusively by cybercriminals for providing complete anonymity. [...]
json.contentSnippet: The police in the Netherlands have seized around 250 physical servers powering a bulletproof hosting service in the country used exclusively by cybercriminals for providing complete anonymity. [...]

json.creator: Sergiu Gatlan
json.title: Microsoft: Azure hit by 15 Tbps DDoS attack using 500,000 IP addresses
json.dc:creator: Sergiu Gatlan
json.content: Microsoft said today that the Aisuru botnet hit its Azure network with a 15.72 terabits per second (Tbps) DDoS attack, launched from over 500,000 IP addresses. [...]
json.contentSnippet: Microsoft said today that the Aisuru botnet hit its Azure network with a 15.72 terabits per second (Tbps) DDoS attack, launched from over 500,000 IP addresses. [...]

json.creator: Ax Sharma
json.title: DoorDash email spoofing vulnerability sparks messy disclosure dispute
json.dc:creator: Ax Sharma
json.content: A vulnerability in DoorDash's systems could allow anyone to send "official" DoorDash-themed emails right from company's authorized servers, paving a near-perfect phishing channel. DoorDash has now patched the issue, but a contentious disclosure dispute has erupted, with both sides accusing each other of acting in bad faith. [...]
json.contentSnippet: A vulnerability in DoorDash's systems could allow anyone to send "official" DoorDash-themed emails right from company's authorized servers, paving a near-perfect phishing channel. DoorDash has now patched the issue, but a contentious disclosure dispute has erupted, with both sides accusing each other of acting in bad faith. [...]

json.dc:creator: Sergiu Gatlan
json.content: The office of Pennsylvania's attorney general has confirmed that the ransomware gang behind an August 2025 cyberattack stole files containing personal and medical information. [...]
